# RetroFoot Project Overview

## Monorepo Structure

- `apps/web` - React 19 + Vite frontend (Cloudflare Pages)
- `apps/api` - Hono API backend (Cloudflare Workers)
- `packages/core` - Pure TypeScript game engine (no dependencies)
- `packages/db` - Drizzle ORM schema + migrations (Cloudflare D1)

## Import Patterns

```typescript
import type { Player, Team } from '@retrofoot/core/types'
import { createDb } from '@retrofoot/db'
import { players } from '@retrofoot/db/schema'
```

## Deployment

- Frontend: Cloudflare Pages (auto-deploy on push to main)
- Backend: Cloudflare Workers (wrangler deploy)
- Database: Cloudflare D1 (SQLite)
- Migrations: `pnpm --filter @retrofoot/db generate` then `wrangler d1 migrations apply`

## Key Constraints

- No real team/player names (fictional only)
- Workers limit: 10ms CPU, 128MB memory
- D1 limit: 5GB storage, 5M reads/day (free tier)
- Core package must have zero dependencies and no I/O
